📥 Complete Download & Setup Guide
🎯 All Files You Need to Download

I've created 13 files for you. Here's how to get them all:
📂 File Structure

Create this folder structure on your computer:

justice-client-portal/
├── server.js
├── package.json
├── database.sql
├── Dockerfile
├── docker-compose.yml
├── .dockerignore
├── README.md
├── QUICKSTART.md
├── DOCKER.md
└── public/
    ├── front.html
    ├── new.html
    ├── update.html
    └── find.html

📝 Step-by-Step Download Instructions
Step 1: Create Project Folder

Windows:
cmd

mkdir C:\Projects\justice-client-portal
cd C:\Projects\justice-client-portal
mkdir public

Mac/Linux:
bash

mkdir -p ~/Projects/justice-client-portal/public
cd ~/Projects/justice-client-portal

Step 2: Download Each File

Look at the artifacts I created above in our conversation. Each one has a title like "Backend Server (server.js)". Here's what to do:
🔵 Root Folder Files (Copy to justice-client-portal/)

    server.js (Docker-Ready version)
        Artifact title: "server.js (Docker-Ready)"
        Click the artifact → Copy all text
        Create file: server.js
        Paste and save
    package.json
        Artifact title: "Package.json"
        Click → Copy → Create file → Paste → Save
    database.sql
        Artifact title: "Database Setup (database.sql)"
        Click → Copy → Create file → Paste → Save
    Dockerfile
        Artifact title: "Dockerfile"
        Click → Copy → Create file → Paste → Save
        ⚠️ Important: File name is Dockerfile (no extension!)
    docker-compose.yml
        Artifact title: "docker-compose.yml"
        Click → Copy → Create file → Paste → Save
    .dockerignore
        Artifact title: ".dockerignore"
        Click → Copy → Create file → Paste → Save
        ⚠️ Important: File starts with a dot!
    README.md (Optional but recommended)
        Artifact title: "Complete Setup Instructions (README.md)"
        Click → Copy → Create file → Paste → Save
    QUICKSTART.md (Optional)
        Artifact title: "Quick Start Guide (QUICKSTART.md)"
        Click → Copy → Create file → Paste → Save
    DOCKER.md (Optional)
        Artifact title: "Docker Setup Guide (DOCKER.md)"
        Click → Copy → Create file → Paste → Save

