🚀 Choose Your Setup Method
Option A: Docker Setup (Easiest - Recommended)

Requirements:

    Docker Desktop installed

Steps:
bash

cd justice-client-portal

# Start everything
docker-compose up -d

# Wait 30 seconds, then open browser
# http://localhost:3000

That's it! ✅ No MySQL installation needed!
Option B: Traditional Setup

Requirements:

    Node.js installed
    MySQL installed

Steps:
bash

cd justice-client-portal

# 1. Install dependencies
npm install

# 2. Create database
mysql -u root -p
CREATE DATABASE law_department;
exit;

# 3. Edit server.js line 17 (set MySQL password)
# password: 'your_mysql_password_here'

# 4. Start server
npm start

# 5. Open browser
# http://localhost:3000

🎯 Quick Test

After setup, test each feature:

    ✅ Home Page - Should show 3 cards
    ✅ Add New Case - Fill form and submit
    ✅ Find Case - Search for the case you added
    ✅ Update Case - Search and edit the case

🐛 Common Issues
Issue: "File not found"

    Solution: Make sure filenames match exactly (case-sensitive on Linux/Mac)
    Check for extra spaces in filenames

Issue: "Cannot find module"

    Solution: Run npm install in project folder

Issue: Copying artifact text includes line numbers

    Solution: Most text editors add line numbers only for display
    If they're actually copied, remove them manually

Issue: Special characters look weird

    Solution: Save files with UTF-8 encoding
    In Notepad++: Encoding → Convert to UTF-8

