🆘 Need Help?

If you're stuck:

    Check artifact names - Make sure you're copying the right version
    Verify file structure - Use the checklist above
    Check file contents - Files should start with specific text:
        server.js → const express = require('express');
        front.html → <!DOCTYPE html>
        package.json → {
    Try Docker first - It's easier and more reliable

✅ Success Criteria

You'll know you've downloaded everything correctly when:

    All 13 files exist in correct locations
    File sizes match approximately
    npm install runs without errors (traditional setup)
    docker-compose up -d runs without errors (Docker setup)
    Can access http://localhost:3000
    Can see home page with 3 cards
    Can add, find, and update cases

🎉 You're Ready!

Once you have all files downloaded:

With Docker:
bash

docker-compose up -d

Without Docker:
bash

npm install
npm start

Then open: http://localhost:3000

Happy coding! 🚀
